The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 December is 12,583 (1,456.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 December, there were 1,597 new confirmed cases (184.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 December, there were 824 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 94% (773 extra cases).
